IR2 studies the distribution of interplanetary dust in the 0.7–1.0 AU region from the Sun by observing the zodiacal light at 1.65 μm (astronomical H-band). Sensitivity is required to detect the typical flux of ∼4×10-7(Wm-2sr-1)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
